            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <p>The conferring of the Companionship of the Order<lb break="yes"/>of the Bath on the African traveller, Dr. Barth, who<lb break="yes"/>is a native of this city, of which intelligence was<lb break="yes"/>received yesterday, has given great satisfaction here,<lb break="yes"/>not only on account of his being a citizen, but be-<lb break="no"/>cause throughout Germany great interest is felt in<lb break="yes" />all that is connected with African discovery; in<lb break="yes"/>which service, besides Dr. Barth, M. Vogel, Dr.<lb break="yes"/>Overweg, and other Germans are to be found who<lb break="yes"/>have also greatly distinguished themselves. A recent<lb break="yes"/>circumstance has shown how much the veteran<lb break="yes" />Humboldt is interested in the still uncertain fate of<lb break="yes"/>Vogel, to whose father at Leipsic M. Humboldt has<lb break="yes"/>addressed the following touching and characteristic<lb break="yes"/>letter:&#x2014;</p>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <floatingText>
                <body>
                    <div n="2" type="letter">
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;Berlin, Nov. 7.</hi>
                        </dateline>
                        <lb break="yes"/>
                        <p>&#x201C;What has been transmitted to me direct from the<lb break="yes" />British Consulate at Tripoli, by direction of Lord Malmes-<lb break="no"/>bury, is of great interest, because it proves that no possible<lb break="yes"/>means are neglected that can lead to obtaining correct in-<lb break="no"/>formation, even from the chiefs of the Tuariks. The pro-<lb break="no"/>posal to visit the prisons of Wada&#x00EF; is a sure guarantee for<lb break="yes"/>this, fortified as it is by the assurance that no money will be<lb break="yes"/>spared. Have confidence, then, you and the afflicted<lb break="yes"/>mother, in the assistance of God, and through that in the<lb break="yes"/>help of man. The King, ill as he was when he returned<lb break="yes"/>from Tegernsee, was nevertheless most warmly interested<lb break="yes"/>in all that relates to your Edward.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <salute>&#x2014;Yours faithfully,<lb break="yes"/>
                                <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Humboldt,</hi>
                                    <lb break="yes"/>Scarcely half convalescent.&#x201D;</hi>
                            </salute>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body>
            </floatingText>
        </body>
        <back/>
    </text>
